  "text_preview": "\"rat\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► RAT : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"rat\" To do the sign for \"rat,\" brush your nose twice with an \"R\" hand. In context it is possible to do this sign with just an index finger instead of the \"R.\" But lacking context, the \"R\" hand makes it clear that you mean \"rat\" and not mouse. The sign for \"rat\" is thus an initialized version of the sign for \"mouse.\" You will see the sign MOUSE done with either an index finger or a pinkie, but I recommend you stick with the index finger for mouse and the \"R\" hand for RAT. (Unless your local Deaf or ASL instructor has some other preference). RAT: Note: The sign RAT is also sometimes used to mean \"freshman.\" This is likely due to the Gallaudet Universit"
}
